### Why

v1.4.0 was released and validated clean. Ran a follow-up re-audit on the same ArchIdeas corpus within hours. Found four residue tokens in 2 files that evaded all three v1.4.0 grep classes. Pattern diagnosis: review-process vocabulary ("per review", "after review") leaks into edited text as parenthetical qualifiers, and the v1.4.0 semantic-judgment class only covers direct correction words, not review-process metadata. This is a generic hazard — any corpus that has been through human/agent review will carry this residue sub-class.

